OL,3,CPolice watchdog brands criminal
OL,4,Cjustice system 'dysfunctional'
OL,6,FThe criminal justice system is
OL,7,F"undoubtedly dysfunctional", the
OL,8,Fpolice watchdog has said, as he
OL,9,Fdescribed the lack of prison places as
OL,10,Fa "nightmare".
OL,12,FHis Majesty's Chief Inspector of
OL,13,FConstabulary Andy Cooke told The
OL,14,FSunday Telegraph that "too often"
OL,15,Fpolice officers are "getting the
OL,16,Fbasics wrong", such as failing to
OL,17,Fanswer the phone quickly or respond to
OL,18,Fincidents at pace.
