OL,6,FThe Government has said that those who
OL,7,Fare released will serve the rest of
OL,8,Ftheir sentence under strict licensing
OL,9,Fconditions.
OL,11,FOn prison places, Mr Cooke said: "It
OL,12,Fis a nightmare. There's no easy option
OL,13,Fbecause there are not enough prison
OL,14,Fspaces.
OL,16,F"The Government had no choice other
OL,17,Fthan to release people early, but it
OL,18,Fdoes put a strain on the rest of the
OL,19,Fsystem, because probation are
OL,20,Funderstaffed and underfunded."
